.TH "rpc_create_client_dir" 9 "rpc_create_client_dir" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpc_create_client_dir \- Create a new rpc_client directory in rpc_pipefs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct dentry *" rpc_create_client_dir
.BI "(struct dentry *dentry "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "struct rpc_clnt *rpc_client "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dentry" 12
the parent of new directory
.IP "name" 12
the name of new directory
.IP "rpc_client" 12
rpc client to associate with this directory
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This creates a directory at the given \fIpath\fP associated with
\fIrpc_clnt\fP, which will contain a file named "info" with some basic
information about the client, together with any "pipes" that may
later be created using \fBrpc_mkpipe\fP.
